{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:41.080140+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e39e158f2cced5a68cc724fd8a0d51b0f066d064)", "id": "lc_e8f98f57-f584-4ae2-a7ff-f50c658bf644"}, {"type": "text", "text": "name: CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ \"main\" ]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ \"main\" ]\n\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up JDK\n        uses: actions/setup-java@v3\n        with:\n          java-version: '21'\n          distribution: 'adopt'\n      - name: Lint\n        uses: gradle/gradle-build-action@67421db6bd0bf253fb4bd25b31ebb98943c375e1\n        with:\n          arguments: checkFormat\n      - name: Test\n        uses: gradle/gradle-build-action@67421db6bd0bf253fb4bd25b31ebb98943c375e1\n        with:\n          arguments: test\n", "id": "lc_a77c3dd9-e636-44bf-bc91-9d4d702e5cca"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "ca7e1a6d-bfc2-4fb2-a2f8-9a77aa71f9a4", "tool_call_id": "call_3da4e53a61d84bb3ac9d34dd", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:41.371953+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ae2fee1a95d4ef3b1bae148cbdbc4f0d9726b694)", "id": "lc_d8ccb08a-f81c-4cf8-bc6b-118159d975b9"}, {"type": "text", "text": "subprojects {\n    apply plugin: 'java'\n    apply plugin: 'io.spring.javaformat'\n\n    dependencies {\n        compileOnly \"io.spring.javaformat:spring-javaformat-gradle-plugin:${springJavaFormatVersion}\"\n    }\n}", "id": "lc_10072f14-140b-40ef-adcb-601a68176099"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "eabecc4a-feb5-464c-81e8-d400b82f2fa0", "tool_call_id": "call_f7c41e9d4329488b80cf1c81", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:17:01.684857+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## How testing is organized in this template\n\n### 1. Default test execution uses JUnit tags and excludes developer-only tests\n\nIn `build.gradle`, every `subproject` configures the default `test` task like this:\n\n```groovy\ntest {\n    useJUnitPlatform {\n        excludeTags 'develop', 'restdocs'\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSo by default:\n- `./gradlew test` **excludes** tests tagged `develop` and `restdocs`.\n- Standard unit/integration tests that are **not** tagged run in the default `test` task.\n- Developer-only tests and REST-docs-oriented tests are intentionally excluded from the default execution.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Named test tasks are defined via Gradle Test Suites\n\nThe template also defines **four named test suite targets** inside `testing.suites.test.targets`, each backed by its own test task. All are placed in the `verification` group:\n\n| Named target | Tag strategy | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `unitTest` | `includeTags` nothing special; **excludes** `'develop', 'context', 'restdocs'` | Fast unit-level tests only |\n| `contextTest` | `includeTags 'context'` | Tests that likely verify Spring context loading / wiring |\n| `restDocsTest` | `includeTags 'restdocs'` | API documentation / REST Docs tests |\n| `developTest` | `includeTags 'develop'` | Developer-only / local-dev tests |\n\nKey points:\n- `unitTest` is explicitly narrower than the default `test` task, because it also excludes `context`.\n- `contextTest`, `restDocsTest`, and `developTest` are **inclusive** by tag.\n- This creates a clear separation by responsibility:\n  - fast unit checks,\n  - context/wiring checks,\n  - documentation tests,\n  - local-only experiments.\n\n---\n\n### 3. REST Docs tests are wired into documentation generation\n\nThere is also this dependency wiring:\n\n```groovy\ntasks.named('asciidoctor').configure {\n    dependsOn restDocsTest\n}\n```\n\nThat means:\n- Documentation generation depends on REST Docs tests.\n- The template treats REST Docs tests as part of the docs pipeline, not just generic verification.\n\n---\n\n### 4. CI-oriented execution differs from local/develop execution\n\nThe GitHub Actions workflow in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` runs:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Lint\n  arguments: checkFormat\n- name: Test\n  arguments: test\n```\n\nSo in CI:\n- The pipeline first enforces formatting.\n- Then it runs `test`, which **does not** execute `develop` or `restdocs` tests.\n\nThis makes CI behavior:\n- **Stricter on formatting**\n- **Focused on core test stability**\n- **Excluding developer-only tests** that may be experimental/local\n- **Excluding REST Docs tests**, unless some other step or local workflow runs them explicitly\n\nBy contrast, developers locally can run the specialized tasks:\n- `./gradlew developTest` for local/dev-only tests\n- `./gradlew contextTest` for context tests\n- `./gradlew restDocsTest` for REST docs tests\n- `./gradlew unitTest` for pure unit tests\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis template organizes testing around **JUnit 5 tags** and **Gradle named test tasks**:\n\n- Default `test` excludes **`develop`** and **`restdocs`**\n- `unitTest` excludes **`develop`, `context`, `restdocs`**\n- `contextTest` runs only **`context`**\n- `restDocsTest` runs only **`restdocs`**\n- `developTest` runs only **`develop`**\n- CI runs **lint + `test`**, so it intentionally avoids developer-only and REST-docs tests\n- Local developers can explicitly run the more specialized test tasks when needed\n\nIf you want, I can also map these tag-based categories to the actual test classes in the repo.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 943, "prompt_tokens": 9684, "total_tokens": 10627, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 100, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9152, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0010847772, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002643672, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00082041}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863401-31J3yBvxgSV6N8EbKOPr", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3ba-fd9c-74c1-8d23-602b44bab798-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9684, "output_tokens": 943, "total_tokens": 10627, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9152}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 100}}}}]}}}
